The Lenzing Group is a world market leader headquartered in Austria, with production sites in all major markets as well as a worldwide network of sales and marketing offices. Lenzing supplies the global textile and nonwovens industry with sustainable high-quality, botanic cellulose fibers. Its portfolio ranges from dissolving pulp to standard and specialty cellulose fibers. In addition to its core business of fibers, the Lenzing Group also operates in the field of engineering and plant construction. The Global Marketing and Branding function based in Hong Kong manages the portfolio of consumer ingredient brands including TENCEL(TM) and LENZING(TM) ECOVERO(TM) for fashion and home products, VEOCEL(TM) for wipes, beauty, and hygiene products. Our portfolio of branded fibers are well-positioned to leverage the global trend of environmental protection and mounting consumer demand for sustainable and quality ingredient brands. The Lenzing Group invites applications for the position of Brand Manager LENZING™ ECOVERO™ to be based in Hong Kong. 

Reporting to the Head of Global Brand Management, the successful candidate would be responsible mainly for:



Define & execute global brand strategy for LENZING™ ECOVERO™, incl. process for branding support to new product launches and development of global campaigns on brand activation. Develop brand content of assigned projects globally & regionally, manage access to brand assets;
Take responsibility for overall brand performance incl. benchmarking and reporting systems and drive consistency of brand usage throughout the organization;
Align with retail brands for co-branding activities;
Support and guide regional marketing teams, to ensure a powerful brand activation and execution for regional communications plans and collaborate with the legal team for trademark protection & licensing;
Align internal & external partners, media & licensees to ensure execution of branding initiatives;
Support brand management process on TX Branding Guidelines, claims, and brand materials development including claims and swing tag system;
Support in assigned global brand projects including retailer education and E-learning. 
Our expectations for this exciting role:


10+ years of experience in Brand Management in consumer-driven /FMCG /Branded Fashion industry or related industry with A-brands;
Proven track record in brand strategy development;
Experience in 360 global brand activation management;
A result-oriented experienced brand marketer with a strong business drive;
Exceptional communication and influencing skills in English.

The annual compensation for this position will fit regional practice and depends on qualifications and experience. Additionally, you will also take part in the Lenzing Group bonus system.

Take the chance to contribute to the success of Lenzing Group's new consumer-first strategy! We look forward to your application.

